               <p>WILLIAM EASTMAN. I am a <rs id="t18280221-312-viclabel1649" type="occupation">spice-merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-312-victim1722 t18280221-312-viclabel1649"></join>, and live in Little Distaff-lane. I was in <placeName id="t18280221-312-crimeloc1650">Tower Royal</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-312-crimeloc1650" type="placeName" value="Tower Royal"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-312-crimeloc1650" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-312-off1647 t18280221-312-crimeloc1650"></join>, between six and seven o'clock in the evening, on the 20th of February, walking with my partner, who felt somebody touch him; he said to me "Somebody is picking your pocket;" I turned round and saw the prisoner putting my handkerchief into his bosom. I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-312-person1723">
                  RICHARD 
                  GEORGE STATHAM
               <interp inst="t18280221-312-person1723" type="surname" value="GEORGE STATHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-312-person1723" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-312-person1723" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took him to this watch-house: he said he did it through distress, and that he had no food all day.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182802210145"></xptr>Prisoner's Defence. I was out of employ; I saw the gentleman's handkerchief touching the ground; I took it up, intending to give it to him.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 21.</p>
               <p>
